Ben Manes mentioned not needing to be concerned about the ABA problem in a language with garbage collection.  For those interested in this in the future, there&#39;s [this article](http://www.hergert.me/blog/2009/12/25/intro-to-lock-free-wait-free-and-aba.html) which is a nice read.  The important part:

&gt; In garbage collected languages this isn&#39;t a problem. Why? Because the node&#39;s memory cannot be reclaimed for a new object until observing threads containing pointers to the structure have released them.

